@AngryPowman As @gautam1858 notes, you can build TF for all supported mobile architectures, including arm64-v8a, with Bazel.

These libraries are also published in the [prebuilt nightly libs](https://ci.tensorflow.org/view/Nightly/job/nightly-android/) and the TensorFlow AAR also contains them (usage described [here](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/tree/master/tensorflow/contrib/android)), which is the recommended way of integrating TF if you don't need custom functionality.

We don't have build support for architectures other than armeabi-v7a using the Makefile build yet, but user contributions are welcome to remedy that.
